  "bio": [
    "Stefan Kaluzny founded Sycamore Partners in 2011. The private equity firm now manages more than $13 billion in assets",
    "Sycamore has invested in consumer and retail brands including department store chain Belk, office supply retailer Staples and fast-fashion chain Hot Topic.",
    "Sycamore led the acquisition of drugstore giant Walgreens in a $10 billion transaction in 2025.",
    "The son of a pianist and a teacher, Kaluzny grew up on the Lower East Side of Manhattan and earned a bachelor's degree from Yale and an MBA from Harvard.",
    "He worked as a consultant at Bain & Co. but in 1994 left to cofound Delray Farms, a chain of fresh grocery stores serving low-income Hispanic communities in Chicago."
